&lt;p&gt;Axonius, Inc. (Remote, reporting to headquarters in New York, NY) is seeking a DevOps Tech Lead. This role involves defining and creating complex technological solutions to address issues raised by the entire company in order to enhance Axonius&#39; proprietary platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Specifically, the DevOps Tech Lead is responsible for designing and implementing Axonius&#39; complex and unique tools and solutions in the following areas:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads the design of the company’s cloud infrastructure architecture, from the organizational account structure to the deployment of individual workloads. Defines where and how services run, and how they integrate with dependent systems across the platform. Establishes scalable, secure, and resilient infrastructure patterns;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads the design and configuration of the networking architecture supporting distributed services across the Axonius platform. Defines scalable and secure network topologies and connectivity patterns within AWS environments. Architects the use and integration of services such as Application Load Balancers, Network Load Balancers, NAT and Internet Gateways, and VPC and S3 endpoints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads the design and development of the company’s Infrastructure as Code frameworks, enabling consistent and automated infrastructure provisioning across environments. Architects scalable deployment patterns using Terraform and AWS CloudFormation. Establishes standards and reusable modules to ensure reliability, maintainability, and governance of cloud infrastructure;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designs and maintains CI automation for continuous integration and delivery, enabling software development, testing, and deployment;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads the design and governance of the company’s end-to-end Configuration Management architecture, ensuring scalable, reliable, and auditable system configurations across all environments. Defines standards &amp;amp; automation strategies to maintain consistency and operational excellence, mainly utilizing Ansible;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architects and governs the company’s local and staging development environments, delivering a scalable, consistent developer experience across diverse hardware and operating systems. Designs flexible, multi-purpose solutions and rollout strategies to support 200+ internal users. Establishes standards, automation, and tooling to streamline setup, testing, and environment parity;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads the design of the company’s end-to-end monitoring architecture, defining how the full monitoring stack is built, deployed, and operated. Establishes standards for metrics, logs, and telemetry collection to ensure comprehensive visibility across systems and services. Designs scalable solutions that enable reliable observability and actionable insights. Ensures the monitoring platform effectively serves internal teams and drives operational excellence;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads the evaluation and introduction of new DevOps tools across the organization, ensuring the platform stack remains modern, efficient, and aligned with engineering needs. Conducts research, proof-of-concepts, and technical assessments to identify solutions that deliver the greatest operational impact. Drives adoption of tools across domains such as cloud infrastructure, CI/CD, configuration management, AWS automation, and monitoring.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position requires at least 9 years of experience as a DevOps or VoIP engineer, which also includes experience with the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;9 years of experience:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing and maintaining Linux-based servers, which includes any experience with tools such as SaltStack, Kubernetes, or writing in Bash;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 years of experience:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing and maintaining Linux-based Web-Servers, such as Apache, Nginx,

&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;1&quot;&gt;The Director of Global IT Operations will lead our global IT Support and Systems Administration teams, serving as the strategic &quot;face of IT&quot; for a rapidly growing workforce. Reporting to the VP of Global IT &amp;amp; Systems, you will mature our service-facing technical functions by balancing high-level strategy with hands-on technical excellence. This role is pivotal in driving an automation-first culture that reduces user friction while maintaining a robust security posture across a cloud-native environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 data-path-to-node=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;3,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Strategic Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Manage and mentor a global, multi-site team of IT Support Engineers and Systems Administrators across the US and Israel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;3,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Operational Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive daily operations and long-term roadmaps for support services, ensuring high-touch service delivery and metric-driven performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;3,2,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Automation &amp;amp; AI:&lt;/strong&gt; Identify and implement AI-driven tools and automation frameworks for onboarding, offboarding, and routine ticket resolution to enhance efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3,3,0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;3,3,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Cross-Functional Partnership:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as a diplomat between IT and business departments to ensure IT is viewed as a strategic partner and enabler.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 data-path-to-node=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;5&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;5,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Extensive Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; 5+ years of experience leading global IT support and system administration teams in a high-growth technology company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;5,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Technical Foundations:&lt;/strong&gt; 10+ years of total IT experience with at least 8 years in hands-on systems administration or IT operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;5,2,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Global Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Proven experience managing geographically dispersed teams (specifically US and EMEA) and a remote-first fleet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5,3,0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;5,3,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Language Proficiency:&lt;/strong&gt; Full professional English fluency for global stakeholder management and executive communication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;7,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;7,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Advanced SaaS Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt; Expert-level knowledge of Okta, Google Workspace, Slack, Zoom, and Zendesk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;7,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;7,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Modern MDM Mastery:&lt;/strong&gt; Hands-on experience managing macOS and Windows environments, specifically using Jamf and Intune.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 data-path-to-node=&quot;6&quot;&gt;Preferred

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enterprise Account Executive: Arizona&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a high-performing Enterprise Account Executive to lead enterprise sales efforts across the Arizona and New Mexico region, targeting large enterprise organizations above 2,000 employees. This is a pivotal role requiring a strong work ethic, relentless drive, and purposeful daily activity to build and maintain a robust pipeline and exceed revenue targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate thrives in a fast-paced, high-output environment, demonstrates ownership of their territory, and executes with precision and urgency. This individual will collaborate closely with senior sales leadership, channel partners, and cross-functional teams to drive value-based sales engagements that solve complex IT and security challenges for major customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute a comprehensive regional strategy designed to deliver a 4x pipeline relative to quota.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate with a bias for action and a focus on measurable outcomes, holding yourself accountable to activity goals and performance benchmarks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and nurture strong channel and security/IT vendor partnerships, leveraging their reach and influence to accelerate growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualify and advance opportunities using value-based selling methodologies and frameworks such as MEDDPIC, ensuring clear business value alignment with customer needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain high-quality hygiene in Salesforce and Clari, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistent and insightful Chatter posts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear, strategic next steps for all active opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Up-to-date MEDDPIC criteria&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurate and timely forecasting with realistic close dates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of success in a closing role selling to Enterprise accounts, with a proven hunter mentality and consistent quota attainment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing and closing complex, multi-stakeholder sales cycles within large organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to build and execute a regional go-to-market strategy, coordinating effectively with channel partners, tech alliances, BDRs, SEs, Marketing, and Product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong working knowledge of enterprise IT and security environments, including solutions like endpoint protection, vulnerability management, SIEM, CMDB, Active Directory, firewalls, cloud platforms, and SaaS offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong negotiation skills with a history of driving value-based deals and minimizing discounting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly self-motivated and proactive, with the ability to work independently and efficiently in a remote, field-based environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A disciplined operator who understands the importance of CRM hygiene, structured deal execution, and precision in forecasting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates a strong work ethic, integrity, and a commitment to excellence in every customer interaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive spirit and a deep drive to win, not just against quota, but in delivering transformational outcomes for customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinker with resourcefulness and the ability to adapt and thrive in dynamic, fast-evolving conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is more than a sales job, this is a high-impact role for someone ready to own their business, execute at a high level, and be a key contributor to the company’s growth in a top-tier market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
